```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "environment": "paccmann_predict",
    "python_script": "/nas/longleaf/home/qhz/paccmann_predictor/examples/IC50/train_paccmann.py",
    "input_files": [
      "gdsc_old/mask_drug/maskdrug_train_${SLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID}.csv",
      "gdsc_old/mask_drug/maskdrug_test_${SLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID}.csv",
      "gdsc_old/gdsc_gene_exp.csv",
      "gdsc_old/gdsc_smile.smi",
      "data/2128_genes.pkl",
      "single_pytorch_model/smiles_language",
      "single_pytorch_model/model_params_50.json"
    ],
    "output_file": "gdsc1_maskdrug_${SLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID}",
    "resources": {
      "partition": "general",
      "nodes": 1,
      "memory": "51200",
      "cpus": 1,
      "time": "200:00:00",
      "email": "qhz@email.unc.edu",
      "email_type": "end",
      "array_tasks": "1-10"
    }
  }
}
```

This script uses the **SLURM** workload manager to run a Python script on a cluster. The script uses the `paccmann_predict` environment and relies on several input files, including gene expression data, chemical structures, and model parameters. The script runs for a maximum of 200 hours and is executed for 10 different tasks (array tasks 1-10).
